Jakadan Amurka ya zargi kasar Sin da yin tawaye da tallace-tallace masu tayar da hankali
Wata mako bayan da wani jaridar kasar Sin ta wallafa wani sanarwa a cikin jaridar Amurka, wanda ya yaba da amfanin cinikin Amurka da China, jakadan Amurka a China, Beijing, ya zargi amfani da jaridar Amurka don yada propaganda.
A ranar Lahadi da ta gabata, shugaban Amurka Donald Trump ya ambaci wani karin bayani da aka samu daga jaridar China Daily a cikin jaridar Des Moines Register, wadda ta fi kowa samun tallafi a jihar Iowa, bayan da kasar Sin ta zargi kasar ta da tsoma baki a zaben Amurka na ranar 6 ga watan Nuwamba, abin da kasar Sin ta musanta.
Rahoton da kamfanin dillancin labarai na Reuters ya wallafa ya nuna cewa jami'an gwamnatin Amurka sun bayyana zargin da Trump ya yi wa Beijing na kokarin tsoma baki a zaben Amurka a matsayin wani sabon mataki a kokarin da Washington ke yi na matsa lamba a kan kasar Sin.
Ko da yake yin tallan tallace-tallace na kasuwanci na al'ada ne ga gwamnatocin ƙasashen waje, Beijing da Washington suna cikin rikici a halin yanzu a cikin ƙara yawan yaƙin kasuwanci, inda suke musayar juna ta hanyar sanya haraji a kan kayayyakin da aka shigo da su.
